      "text": [
        " رِوَايَةِ اِبْنِ بُكَيْرٍ عَنْ زُرَارَةَ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ قَالَ: \"فِي اَلْإِصْبَعِ عَشْرٌ مِنَ اَلْإِبِلِ إِذَا قُطِعَتْ مِنْ أَصْلِهَا أَوْ شَلَّتْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5297 - In the narration of Ibn Bukayr from Zurara from Abu Abdullah (as), he said:\n\"For each finger, there is a compensation of ten camels if it is cut off from its base or becomes paralyzed.\""
        ]
      }
    },
